snippet.textDisplay:
Just to add a few notes


1. No confirmation that the virus originated from the wet market. It’s quite a controversial topic right now and many conspiracy stories being thrown around that include bioengineering. Time will tell.

2. Hygiene, hygiene, hygiene...Learn it. Live it. Love it. It’s the only way to protect yourself until a vaccine is developed.
Also, keep your distance from those who have symptoms of fever and cough. Better safe than sorry.

3. Surgical masks only protect others from you if YOU are infected. It doesn’t protect YOU from those who are infected. If you want to protect yourself, you need a certified N95 or higher rated mask. You can find these at a local drug store or even Home Depot. Granted, in the US, there’s no reason to wear these...yet.

4. Vaccine development will be very difficult because this novel coronavirus is a RNA virus which means it replicates and evolves rapidly. This means that we will need multiple vaccines for different geographical locations. A universal vaccine won’t be possible.

5. WHO just labeled this virus a global emergency. Reiterating what Dr. Mike said, don’t travel to China!

6. If you want to stay up to date on the outbreak, find infectious disease epidemiologists on Twitter that you can follow. There are a lot of smart people out there providing groundbreaking news.
